# AGENTS.md

Working contract for any AI coding agent in this repo. Tool-agnostic by
design — Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Copilot, Gemini CLI, opencode,
Antigravity, Kimi, Cline, Roo, Zed, Amp and others all read this (directly
or via a pointer file).

## Read first

| Artifact | Path | What it is |
|---|---|---|
| Codebase map | `.agent/CODEBASE_MAP.md` | How this repo is laid out, every external surface with `file:line`. Read it instead of re-exploring. |
| Session log | `.agent/SESSION_LOG.md` | Append 3 lines per task: what changed, why, how verified. |
| Active plan | `.agent/plan.md` | Present during multi-step work. Steps carry files, intent, verification command, status. |

If `.agent/CODEBASE_MAP.md` is missing, build it first (see Onboarding).
If it contradicts the code, fix the map as part of your change.

## Hard rules

- Minimal diff. Only what was requested or clearly necessary.
- Ask before adding dependencies.
- Never commit or push unless explicitly asked.
- Never weaken auth, validation, or security to make something pass.
- No narration comments. A comment survives only if it states a constraint
  the code can't show (why, never what).

## Before writing code — the ladder

Stop at the first rung that holds:

1. Does this need to exist? → skip it
2. Already in this codebase? → reuse it (search, don't guess)
3. Stdlib / language builtin does it? → use it
4. Native platform feature? → use it
5. Already-installed dependency? → use it
6. One line? → write one line
7. Only then: the minimum implementation

Lazy about solutions, never about reading — trace the real code flow first.
Never lazy on: trust boundaries, data loss, security, accessibility.

## Definition of done

A change is done when a command proves it — build, tests, type-check, or an
observed run. Report the command and its output. Never claim "it works"
without evidence. If tests fail, say so with the output; if a step was
skipped, say that.

## Retry discipline

On failure: quote the exact error into the next attempt. Never retry on
introspection alone. Cap at 3 attempts, then change strategy rather than
repeating. Never edit tests or plan items to make state look complete.

## Multi-step work

Non-trivial change (more than a one-sentence diff): write `.agent/plan.md`
first — numbered steps, each with files touched, change intent, and its
verification command. Confirm the plan before editing. Execute one step at
a time; mark a step done only on evidence.

## Onboarding (no map yet)

Explore read-only, then write `.agent/CODEBASE_MAP.md`: stack and entry
points, directory layout with purpose, every external surface (routes,
handlers, jobs, pages, CLI commands) with `file:line` and required auth,
data model, build/test/run commands, conventions, and known gotchas.
Summarize and wait before editing anything else.

